name: CoreAPI Deployment_Create
description: API to access the results of Planet 9 Deployment Create
about:
Description

Planet 9-Deployment manage the list of all System and routes for deployment and provides the ability to create the deployment package and request for the approval or to other deployment steps.


API Planet 9-Deployment_Create provides the option to create, delete, the from deployment request from your app.


For the deployment_create process, we have to call the APIs of other artifacts that can be deployed like Launchpad, themes, API, OData, API Group, Packages, and many other Planet 9 artifacts.


Definitions added below are for deploying only one application.

Operations Performed 

Systems/List

Get the Systems- List ( Systems added from Settings_RemoteSystems API)

ResponseSystemsList(array)- Definition

DeployRoutes/List

Get the Routes - List  ( Routes created from API Deployment_Routes)

ResponseDeploymentRoutes(array) - Definition

Deploy/Save

Save the deployment - List ( create the deployment package to transfer from one system to another)

RequestSaveDeployResponse- Definition
ResponseDeploymentRoutes(object) - Definition


WebIDE/GetData

Get WebIDE Data

RequestWebIDEGetDeployData - Definition
ResponseWebIDEGetData- Definition
